@node intro

Introduction


When working a bit with the WB you experience a garbage amount of
directory-windows on your screen - it`s time to start closing all the
unused ones.... :(
Now WarpWB simply closes the parent-window whenever you enter a subdir, so
your screen will be clean and free of waste ;).
You can optionally keep or close the parent-window by pressing a hotkey (see below)
while opening a subdir.


@endnode

@node usage

Usage

Open the Interface via Exchange.
There you can edit the prefs of WarpWB.
if "Close always" is selected, parent window will only be kept when the 
hotkey is pressed. Otherwise the window will close on pressing hotkey.

Now you can select 3 different qualifiers to represent the hotkey.


@endnode

